snippet.textDisplay:
That's shitty. You don't care about learning dog behavior and actually helping your dogs. You just get rid of the problem by getting rid of a dog you had GIFTED to another person (when, if you really wanted to get rid of an animal so badly, you could have gotten rid of one of YOUR OWN that was the actual problem, but you are too selfish to do that). Animals are not toys to discard at the first issue. Especially a dog that you had gifted to someone else (and didn't even let her name him smfh). Neuter and spay your dogs, that's basic responsible pet ownership (people who follow you on other platforms as well confirm you've never said if Shadow was fixed). Learn dog behavior, also basic responsible pet ownership. Actually give a damn about the animals and the people in your life instead of being selfish, entitled pricks. But hey, you've got 9 mln subs so who cares about basic human decency, right? You're above it, I guess.


I just don't understand how you can look at someone being heart-broken over her dog being sent away and think, "sucks to be you, but there's nothing else we can do!", when there absolutely are other options, and ways to have prevented this in the first place. The lack of empathy and respect and effort shown towards the dogs and Maria just baffles me. Disgraceful. Disgusting.
